Voice-call additions (this fork)
--------------------------------
This fork adds Session-to-Session voice-call support. The added calls/
package (introduced on the feat/voice-calls* branches) is licensed
AGPL-3.0-or-later and contains code ported from Session Foundation's
official clients, with attribution and preserved copyright headers:

  - session-android (GPLv3)  — state machine, signaling processor, peer
    connection config, wire message model
  - session-desktop (AGPLv3) — TypeScript call engine, outgoing/incoming
    call message handling

Per-file porting provenance is recorded in calls/COPYING.provenance.

The combined work (forked client plus calls/ package) is distributed under
the terms of the GNU Affero General Public License version 3 (AGPLv3);
GPLv3 Android code combines into an AGPLv3 work per AGPLv3 §13.

Fresh-written core-client patches
---------------------------------
The following patches to the core client are written fresh from the
published SessionProtos.proto field facts (no lines copied from GPL/AGPL
sources) and remain MIT-licensable for contribution upstream to MIT
session.js: the mapCallMessage mapper fix, the CallMessage schema class,
Session.prototype.sendCallMessage, setPollInterval, and NetworkNode.

AGPL §13 — network-use obligation
---------------------------------
Anyone running this code (original + voice-call additions) as a network
service must make the Corresponding Source of the running version
available to users of that service, under the terms of the AGPLv3.
To satisfy this: these repositories are kept public, and releases are
tagged and archived. Service operators embedding this library inherit the
same obligation.

